content:
{
  "plan": "The player has asked about the damage of their arrow attack, but no attack has been declared or resolved yet. The current state is the start of combat, awaiting the player's decision on their action. I will inform the player that they need to declare their action first, then I can help with the damage calculation after the attack roll is known.",
  "narration": "You haven't made an attack yet, Norn. Please tell me your intended action this turn. If you want to shoot your bow, swing your longsword, or do anything else, let me know, and I will guide you through the necessary rolls and inform you of the damage dealt once the attack hits.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Player Norn is taking the Attack action with two attacks using longsword (due to Extra Attack). Player has rolled 11 and 17 adding attack modifier +5 (1 proficiency +3 strength). The first attack total is 16 (11+5) which misses Mimic AC 12 or hits? Assuming AC 12, hits at 16 total, but 11 + 5 = 16 is a hit. 17 + 5 = 22 is a hit too. Calculate damage for both hits using prerolled d8 rolls from the damage dice pool d8: [1,6,6,1,7,6]. We use 1 and 6 for the two damage rolls. Add damage bonus +3 to each. Calculate total damage for each strike, then total damage to Mimic. Subtract total from Mimic HP 58. Update Mimic HP. Mimic is still alive after damage dealt. Mimic attacks next with two attacks. They have two attacks: Pseudopod + Pseudopod Acid. Use prerolled d20 dice in order for their attacks (11 and 3). Mimic attack bonus +5 for Pseudopod. Roll damage dice d8 from the pool for each hit if hit. Process accordingly and apply damage to Norn. Update Norn HP after damage. Narrate full sequence including attacks, rolls, damage, and outcomes. End on player's next turn invitation or round increment as appropriate.",
  "narration": "You grip your longsword tightly, focusing on hitting the mimic twice with your Extra Attack.

First attack roll: You rolled an 11 plus your attack bonus of 5 for a total of 16 against the mimic's AC 12. That hits!

Using the prerolled d8 damage dice, you roll a 1 plus your damage modifier of 3, dealing 4 points of slashing damage.

Second attack roll: You rolled a 17 plus 5, making 22 - a solid hit!

Using the next prerolled d8 damage dice, you roll a 6 plus 3 for a total of 9 points of slashing damage.

The mimic snarls, taking a total of 13 damage. Its form quivers but it remains standing, now at 45 hit points.

The mimic lashes out with its pseudopod!

First attack roll: Using the prerolled d20 of 11 plus 5 attack bonus equals 16.

That hits your AC of 19? Actually, 16 is less than your AC 19, so the attack misses! You deftly parry the blow.

The mimic then attempts an acid pseudopod strike.

Second attack roll: The prerolled d20 is 3 plus 5 equals 8, which misses your AC of 19.

Both attacks miss as you dodge and block its assault.

Your longsword glints as you prepare for your next move, the mimic looming in front of you with 45 hit points remaining.

It's your turn again, Norn. What would you like to do?",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "C05-E1",
        "changes": "Mimic takes 13 slashing damage from Norn's two longsword attacks. HP reduced from 58 to 45."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Avoids all damage from two mimic attacks; HP remains 25."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "The previous round has completed, so combat_round should increment to 2. The narration will clearly state that round 1 has ended and round 2 is beginning. Since the player declared two attacks with their sword, I will prompt for both attack rolls at once, asking the player to roll two d20s and add +5 to each. This improves efficiency and clarity. No other actions will be taken until the player provides rolls and confirms their actions.",
  "narration": "Round 1 has ended. Both you and the mimic have taken your turns.\n\nNow, Round 2 begins.\n\nNorn, you prepare to make your attacks with your longsword. Since you declared two attacks, please roll two d20s and add +5 to each roll for your attack rolls. Let me know the results of both rolls when you're ready.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Correct the combat round tracking by incrementing combat_round to 3 after both Norn and the Mimic have taken their turns in round 2. The previous logic is otherwise correct: Norn's attacks hit for 12 damage total reducing Mimic HP from 45 to 33, Mimic's two attacks both miss, Norn HP remains 25. Narrate all attack rolls, damage rolls, hits, misses, and current HP states, then prompt the player for next action with combat_round incremented to 3.",
  "narration": "You swing your longsword twice with precision.

First attack roll is 14 plus 5 for a total of 19 - that hits the mimic's AC of 12!

Using the prerolled d8 damage dice, you roll a 4 plus your damage modifier of 3, dealing 7 points of slashing damage.

Second attack roll is 16 plus 5, totaling 21 - another hit!

You roll a 2 on your damage die plus 3, dealing 5 points of slashing damage.

The mimic grunts as it takes a total of 12 damage, its form wavering at 33 hit points now.

The mimic lashes out with its pseudopod.

First attack roll: 10 plus 5 equals 15 against your AC 19 - the attack narrowly misses.

Second attack roll: 5 plus 5 equals 10, another miss.

Both mimic attacks fail to connect, leaving you unscathed.

Round 2 has ended. Round 3 begins. Your longsword gleams as you prepare for your next move.

Norn, what is your next action?",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "C05-E1",
        "changes": "Mimic takes 12 slashing damage from Norn's two longsword attacks. HP reduced from 45 to 33."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Avoids all damage from mimic's two pseudopod attacks; HP remains 25."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Process Norn's two attack rolls for this round: 11 + 5 = 16 (hits AC 12) and 15 + 5 = 20 (hits AC 12). Calculate damage for each hit using prerolled d8 from the pool: rolls 7 and 6 plus damage bonus 3 each. Total damage is 10 and 9, total 19. Mimic HP reduces from 33 to 14. Mimic then attacks with two pseudopod attacks using prerolled d20 attack rolls 17 and 15 + 5 = 22 and 20 total (both hit). Roll damage for each attack using damage dice from d8 pool: 3 and 4 plus damage bonus 3 each, total damage 6 and 7, total 13 damage. Norn HP reduces from 25 to 12. Report all rolls, hits, damage calculations, current HP, and end with prompt to player for next turn and increment round to 5.",
  "narration": "You strike the mimic with your longsword twice.

First attack roll: 11 plus 5 equals 16, hitting the mimic's AC 12.

You roll a 7 on your damage die plus 3 for 10 slashing damage.

Second attack roll: 15 plus 5 equals 20, a solid hit!

You roll a 6 plus 3 for 9 slashing damage.

The mimic reels, taking 19 points of damage, its hit points now down to 14.

The mimic retaliates fiercely.

Its first pseudopod attack roll is 17 plus 5 for 22, hitting your AC 19.

Using the prerolled d8, it deals 3 plus 3, totaling 6 bludgeoning damage to you.

The mimic's acid pseudopod strikes next, with an attack roll of 15 plus 5 for 20, also hitting.

It deals 4 plus 3 acid damage, totaling 7.

You take 13 points of damage, your current hit points are now 12.

Round 4 concludes, and Round 5 begins. Your blade hums as you prepare for your next move.

Norn, what will you do?",
  "combat_round": 5,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "C05-E1",
        "changes": "Mimic takes 19 slashing damage from Norn's longsword attacks, HP reduced from 33 to 14."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Takes 13 damage from mimic's pseudopod and acid attacks, HP reduced from 25 to 12."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Player Norn rolled 19 (critical hit) and 7 (normal hit) for attacks this round. Both attacks hit mimic AC 12. For the critical hit, roll double damage dice using prerolled d8: 3 and 5 (+3 damage bonus once). For the normal hit roll damage d8: 7 + 3 damage bonus. Calculate total damage: critical 3+5=8 +3 = 11 damage; normal hit 7+3=10 damage; total 21 damage. Mimic HP reduces from 14 to -7 and is dead. Mimic has no HP left; the battle ends. Narrate the critical hit, damage, mimic's death, and conclude the combat encounter. Use updateEncounter to reflect mimic's death and exit the encounter.",
  "narration": "You strike with deadly precision.\n\nFirst attack roll is a 19 plus 5 for 24 total - that's a critical hit against the mimic's AC 12!\n\nYou roll your damage twice for the critical hit: 3 and 5 on the d8s, plus your damage modifier of 3, dealing a total of 11 slashing damage.\n\nYour second attack roll is a 7 plus 5, totaling 12, still enough to hit.\n\nYou deal 7 plus 3 for 10 slashing damage on this strike.\n\nThe mimic howls in pain as you slice through it for a devastating 21 total damage.\n\nIt collapses, its grotesque form melting back into a shapeless heap on the floor.\n\nThe great hall falls silent once more.\n\nThe mimic is defeated. Well done, Norn.",
  "combat_round": 5,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "C05-E1",
        "changes": "Mimic takes 21 slashing damage from Norn's critical and normal longsword attacks; HP reduced from 14 to -7. Status changed to dead."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "exit",
      "parameters": {}
    }
  ]
}
